Maintenance Planner \& Reliability Engineer

**Country:** Italy

**City:** Origgio (Varese)

**Department:** Global Operations \& Production

**Job ID:** 45327



**Pay Range (full\-time):** EUR 38\.000 \- 58\.000



Management \| Permanent \| Full\-time \| On\-Site



Our people in Manufacturing \& Global Operations share two priorities: getting things done and making things better. If you’re a dynamic person with a positive mindset, you’ll fit in well here. It’s an international team with a powerful spirit of collaboration. Together, we make sure our products meet the highest standards of quality by constantly searching for ways to improve at every stage of our value chain – from the raw materials we buy through to the logistics network that brings our medicines to patients. Join our team and help us make an even bigger contribution to Grünenthal’s future.



What the job looks like



**Each day you’ll enjoy a variety of challenges, such as:**  

In this role, you will be responsible for the site maintenance plan through SAP PM (CMMS) management, maintenance performance monitoring and reliability improvement initiatives, working closely with Engineering, Maintenance and Production global and local teams and leading your Spare Parts team;

Develop maintenance excellence and continuous improvement initiatives by maintaining maintenance engineering reports of KPIs trend and targets;

Monitor and analyze maintenance KPIs, equipment performance, and reliability trends;

Support the Head of Engineering \& Maintenance in the maintenance budget management (Opex \& Capex) and related reporting;

Contribute to technical spare parts optimization and contractor management;

Support procurement activities within the Engineering area;

Ensure compliance with GMP, safety, environmental and corporate requirements;

Maintain and update engineering and maintenance documentation.



What you’ll bring to the table



To make the most of this role and truly thrive, you should have:



Degree in Engineering (Mechanical or Electrical preferred) or equivalent technical background;

3\+ years of experience in maintenance planning within complex industrial environments;

Good knowledge of SAP PM is mandatory;

Understanding of maintenance and operation of manufacturing equipment;

Knowledge of continuous improvement methodologies (TPM, Lean Manufacturing) and of safety regulations (GMP is a plus);

Fluency both in Italian and English;

Strong analytical, communication and ability to work cross\-functionally;

Passion for continuous improvement and operational excellence.

